The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank positive semidefinite matrix from rank-one measurements, which is a problem that arises in various fields such as phase retrieval, covariance sketching, quantum space tomography, and power spectrum estimation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on the mathematical and algorithmic aspects of the problem, Information Theory and Machine Learning seem to be the most likely sub-categories.
